qas.question: Despite being headquartered in Poland, the top-ranking operatives of the Warsaw Pact were from which country?
Which nation was in effective control of both political and military functions of the Warsaw Pact?

plausible_answers.text: the Supreme Commander of the Unified Armed Forces of the Warsaw Treaty Organization

qas.question: Who was also a Second Deputy Minister of Defense of the USSR?

plausible_answers.text: the Chief of Combined Staff of the Unified Armed Forces of the Warsaw Treaty Organization

qas.question: Who was also a Second Deputy Chief of the General Staff of the Armed Forces of the USSR?
Who did not dominate the Warsaw Treaty armed forces?
What committee handled the assigned multi-national forces?

context: The Warsaw Treaty's organization was two-fold: the <b5_0>Political Consultative Committee<b5_0/> handled political matters, and the Combined Command of Pact Armed Forces controlled the assigned multi-national forces, with headquarters in Warsaw, Poland. Furthermore, <b2_0>the Supreme Commander of the Unified Armed Forces of the Warsaw Treaty Organization<b2_0/> which commands and controls all the military forces of the member countries was also a First Deputy Minister of Defense of <a0_0><a1_0>the USSR<a1_0/><a0_0/>, and <b3_0>the Chief of Combined Staff of the Unified Armed Forces of the Warsaw Treaty Organization<b3_0/> was also a First Deputy Chief of the General Staff of the Armed Forces of the USSR. Therefore, although ostensibly an international collective security alliance, the <b4_0>USSR<b4_0/> dominated the Warsaw Treaty armed forces.
